#: ''You can't '''train''' a pig to write poetry.''
# <!--VExercise--> {{intransitive}} To [[improve]] ones [[fitness]].
#: ''I '''trained''' with weights all winter.''
# <!--VProceedInSeq--> To [[proceed]] in [[sequence]].
# <!--VPointInDiffDir--> {{transitive}} To move (a [[gun]]) [[laterally]] so that it points in a different [[direction]].
#: ''The assassin had '''trained''' his gun on the minister.''
# <!--VPosition--> {{transitive}} (Horticulture) To [[encourage]] (a [[plant]] or [[branch]]) to grow in a particular [[direction]] or [[shape]], usually by [[pruning]] and [[bending]].
#: ''The [[vine]] had been '''trained''' over the [[pergola]].''

